llama3.1.reason: The claim is wrong because Nepal Time (NST) was UTC+5:45 from 1986 to 2016, but since the introduction of DST in 2016, Nepal uses NST (UTC+5:45) only during winter, and NPT (UTC+5:30) during summer, which has a one-hour gap with the previous standard time.
